            "content": "Carbon Filtration Systems Maintenance — Filter replacement schedule: Every 6-12 months depending on water quality and usage volume (Tucson's high chlorine shortens carbon life toward 6-month end). System monitoring: Pressure gauges show filter condition—significant pressure drop indicates filter clogging. Taste/odor return signals carbon exhaustion (replace immediately). Water test annually to verify ongoing performance. Replacement procedure: Turn off water supply and relieve system pressure. Unscrew filter housing (some systems have quick-change cartridges). Remove old filter and inspect housing for sediment accumulation. Clean housing if needed, install new genuine Brita PRO filter cartridge. Purge air from system and check for leaks. DIY vs. professional service: Simple cartridge changes: DIY-friendly with basic tools. Complex systems with multiple stages: professional service recommended. Annual professional inspection: recommended for warranty compliance. Costs: Filter cartridges: $80-$150 each (Platinum Series), $150-$250 (Titanium Series). Professional service visit: $150-$200 including labor. Annual cost estimate: $200-$400 depending on system type. Consequence of neglecting maintenance: Reduced contaminant removal (health risk), water flow restriction, bacterial growth in saturated filters, and voided manufacturer warranty."
